# Commit Message Hook Rules

## Format Requirements
- First line should be 50 characters or less
- Use imperative mood in subject line ("Add feature" not "Added feature")
- Capitalize first letter of subject line
- No period at end of subject line
- Blank line between subject and body
- Body lines wrapped at 72 characters

## Commit Types (Conventional Commits)
- feat: New feature
- fix: Bug fix
- docs: Documentation changes
- style: Code style changes (formatting, semicolons, etc)
- refactor: Code refactoring
- perf: Performance improvements
- test: Adding or updating tests
- build: Build system changes
- ci: CI configuration changes
- chore: Maintenance tasks
- revert: Reverting previous commits

## Content Requirements
- Reference issue numbers when applicable (#123)
- Include breaking changes with BREAKING CHANGE:
- Provide context for why the change was made
- List any side effects or consequences

## Prohibited Content
- No profanity or inappropriate language
- No personal information or credentials
- No TODO comments as commit messages
- No WIP (work in progress) commits to main branch

## Examples
```
feat: add user authentication system

Implemented JWT-based authentication with refresh tokens.
Added middleware for protecting routes.

Closes #45
```

```
fix: resolve memory leak in data processor

The data processor was not properly cleaning up listeners,
causing memory to increase over time. Added cleanup in
the destroy method.

Fixes #78
```